The paper deals with learning the structure of Bayesian networks and AMP chain graphs, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. The paper also involves algorithms for finding minimal separators, which is a problem in graph theory and discrete mathematics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves computational independence tests, which fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
